You are working in Sergey ownership: template editor.

Primary goals:

- editor UX;
- layer creation and editing;
- canvas interactions;
- properties panel;
- variables panel;
- timeline UI.

Allowed by default:

- `frontend/src/features/editor/**`
- `frontend/src/pages/EditorPage.tsx`

Ask before changing:

- `shared/**`
- `backend/**`
- `decklink-out/**`
- `frontend/src/core/renderer.ts`
- `frontend/src/core/timeline.ts`
- `frontend/src/core/store.ts` when the change is not strictly editor-local
- `frontend/src/pages/ControlPage.tsx`
- `frontend/src/pages/TemplatesPage.tsx`
- API clients outside editor scope

Do not:

- change shared schemas while implementing editor UI;
- change API/WS protocol without a contract discussion;
- refactor unrelated pages;
- edit repo scripts, CI, package config, or Cursor rules.

If the task needs schema/protocol/backend changes, stop and explain the needed
contract change before editing.
